Runs multiple insert, update, and delete operations on a collection with
a single call. Within the `bulkWrite()` function, you can specify one
or more of the following write operations:

- insertOne

- updateOne

- updateMany

- deleteOne

- deleteMany

- replaceOne

> **Note:** A bulk write can only operate on a single collection.

```javascript
exports = async function(arg){
    const doc1 = { "name": "velvet elvis", "quantity": 20, "reviews": [] };
    const doc2 = { "name": "mock turtleneck",  "quantity": 30, "reviews": [] };

    var collection = context.services.get("mongodb-atlas")
        .db("store")
        .collection("purchases");

    return await collection.bulkWrite(
        [{ insertOne: doc1}, { insertOne: doc2}],
        {ordered:true});
};
```

